A very thought provoking movie.  It really created a barren landscape and the harsh conditions to survive.  Denzel Washington is always up to his best and I liked Mila Kunis.  It was the first time that I saw her in a movie and have found I that she has been in quite a few.  Good action film!

Denzel is D'MAN!! LOVE all his films, there's everything in this film, explosions, gun fights, cannibalism (yet not shown graphically), great fight sequences and... lastly some may ask (as I did upon first viewing this) "Is this a Religious film"?

Well... for those of you, like me, who do not believe in the "supernatural" I would have to answer: Yes - this film IS premised on the foundation of religion BUT (and this is a big but) the "message" I get from the ending (which is totally separated from the rest of the movie) is: OH HORROR of HORRORS! He's starting it ALL OVER AGAIN!!

So, viewed in THAT context (and I'm sure the true believers out there would say that the ending means the "saving" of humankind) I believe the ending statement is the old adage: Those who can not learn from the past, are DOOMED to repeat it.
